---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About Me"
	description="Satellite engineer turned AI & investing enthusiast. PhD, 16 years in space systems, father of two."
	pubDate={new Date('2024-01-01')}
>
	<h2>Hi, I'm Yuta 👋</h2>

	<p>
		I'm a systems engineer with 16 years of hands-on experience in satellite development — from mission
		design and onboard software to ground systems and operations. Over the years I've had the privilege
		of working on spacecraft that actually fly in orbit, and that sense of wonder at what's possible
		beyond our atmosphere has never left me.
	</p>

	<p>
		I hold a <strong>PhD in engineering</strong>, which taught me to dig deep into problems, question
		assumptions, and communicate complex ideas clearly. These habits have shaped how I approach every
		challenge, whether it's debugging a flight software anomaly or building a new side project at
		midnight.
	</p>

	<p>
		These days my curiosity has expanded into two areas I find genuinely exciting:
	</p>

	<ul>
		<li>
			<strong>Artificial Intelligence</strong> — I'm exploring how large language models, agents, and
			AI tooling can augment engineering workflows and open up new products. This blog is partly a
			logbook of that exploration.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Investing &amp; Finance</strong> — From index funds to growth equities, I believe that
			building financial literacy is as important as technical skill. I write about what I learn here
			too.
		</li>
	</ul>

	<p>
		Outside of work and screens, I'm a dad to two wonderful kids who remind me daily that the best
		engineering problems are the ones that make people laugh. We spend a lot of time building LEGO
		spaceships (quality control is strict).
	</p>

	<p>
		This blog is where I share notes from the intersection of space technology, AI, and everyday life.
		If any of it resonates with you, feel free to reach out — I'm always happy to connect with
		engineers, builders, and curious minds.
	</p>
</Layout>

<style>
	h2 {
		color: var(--navy);
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}
	ul {
		padding-left: 1.5em;
		margin-bottom: 1.5em;
	}
	ul li {
		margin-bottom: 0.75em;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}
	strong {
		color: var(--navy);
	}
</style>
